<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="py-14 md:py-20">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="mb-8 text-sm">
        <a class="link" href="/compare">Comparisons</a>
        <span class="mx-2 text-[#5d3a1d]">/</span>
        <span class="text-[#5d3a1d]">Klaviyo vs Mailchimp</span>
      </nav>

      <header class="max-w-4xl">
        <p class="catalog-kicker">Head-to-head</p>
        <h1 class="hero-title mt-5">Klaviyo vs Mailchimp for Shopify email tools</h1>
        <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-[#4a2d17]">
          Mailchimp is the tool your team already knows. Klaviyo is the tool Shopify retention forums insist you need. We evaluated both as full email-tool stacks — newsletters, lifecycle automation, and order-adjacent customer moments — through a specialty tea subscription shop, a climbing-gear retailer with long research cycles, and a vinyl record store still sending sale blasts from a 2019 Mailchimp template. The question is not brand loyalty; it is whether your email layer matches how customers actually buy.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="mt-12 max-w-4xl">
        <TldrBox
          picks={[
            { label: 'Shopify lifecycle', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'Cart, browse, replenishment, and flow revenue attribution built for ecommerce.' },
            { label: 'Familiar editor', tool: 'Mailchimp', reason: 'Low onboarding friction for teams with years of muscle memory.' },
            { label: 'Newsletters + sales', tool: 'Mailchimp', reason: 'Fast broadcast setup before lifecycle complexity arrives.' },
            { label: 'Retention at scale', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'Segmentation and suppression that survive peak season.' },
            { label: 'Middle path', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'Lifecycle playbooks if Klaviyo feels heavy and Mailchimp feels thin.' },
          ]}
        />
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 card overflow-x-auto">
        <h2 class="px-5 py-4 font-serif text-2xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Comparison at a glance</h2>
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Klaviyo</th><th>Mailchimp</th></tr>
          </thead>
