        <h2>What this comparison is actually about</h2>
        <p>
          We stress-tested Klaviyo and Mailchimp with a vinyl record shop doing roughly 350 monthly orders where rare pressings with two-hundred-unit runs shaped the retention calendar. The acute constraint was lifecycle depth across browse cart replenishment and winback. Klaviyo brought Shopify browse and order event depth for collection targeting — valuable when the team had no retention engineer and needed grading-guide PDF offers live before Record Store Day. Mailchimp countered with marketing hub with landing pages surveys and social, which mattered once subscribers existed and VIP allocation drops became a weekly merchandising decision rather than a someday project. Shopify email tools must cover newsletters, lifecycle automation, and transactional-style customer moments without collision; this pairing only works when signup tags, gift-order properties, and recent-purchaser suppressions sync at handoff.
        </p>
        <p>
          Operational discipline separated winners from stack bloat for the same mechanical keyboard vendor. Drop-week and GB close deadlines windows required a documented send priority: transactional-style pre-order confirmations first, active cart recovery second, welcome and education third, promotional broadcasts last. Klaviyo made exclusion filters visible in journey analytics. Mailchimp punished the wrong billing mistake — profile tiers climbing on cold popup imports versus send volume spiking on broadcast-heavy months. Neither platform removes the collision doc taped to ops workflow; both fail when gift purchasers receive replenishment pitches or when SMS and email cart touches fire forty-five minutes apart without shared suppression.
        </p>

